"He was at the Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice fair at some dance party."
“The interesting thing is that his mother wasn’t surprised that his daughter disappeared for 48 hours,” he said.
It is precisely the lack of interest of parents or even their clear tolerance for drinking on the part of their children that is considered the main cause of the increase in alcohol consumption among young people.
Experts point out that, in the case of children, one cannot really talk about dependence.
“An alcoholic is understood to be a person who has been chronically dependent on alcohol for several years, with all the phenomena associated with it, which does not occur in children.”
"In those who drink alcohol repeatedly, it is rather due to a systematically failed social or family environment," explains Chief Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n.
According to the spokesperson Jurinov<0xC3><0xA1>, this year in the pediatric clinic of Motol hospitalized until mid-November forty children drunk.
However, the statistics only show those who come with a serious poisoning and must remain in the hospital.
Young drinkers who, after walking medical recognition, go home with their parents or with the police, do not count.
In addition to the cases where children simply gather after school and drink liquor, there are three seasonal ups and downs for Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n to mention: Witch’s Day, New Year’s Eve and the end of the school year.
"In such a circumstance, they drink from the bad notes or, on the contrary, celebrate the beginning of the holiday."
“On Witch’s Day, I’ve come to see up to seven drunken children at a time,” Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n said.
Drinkers who spend the night in detox under the supervision of doctors, paradoxically, have the advantage that the next day they do not suffer a terrible hangover at home.
Morning headache, caused by dehydration and lack of glucose, is avoided by injecting a serum with glucose and with the nutrients that the body lacks.
"They are much better at it, because after the hectic night, they get up well and it doesn't hurt anything."
“They are only confused about where they are,” Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n notes, adding that patients often lose good humor at least when they see the expenses they have generated.
The transfer by ambulance and hospitalization in a room for serious patients comes to cost tens of thousands of crowns.
“I have often used the cost as a means of educating them, when on the visit I tell them directly to the children how much their intoxication has cost and that they would have to spend the whole summer on a youth job so that you earn enough to pay yourself that night,” Pelik<0xC3><0xA1>n adds.
