His attention on Tweeter coverage is controversial.
In some interviews, some journalists said the complaint about the fact that immediate news was more important than reports delivered more slowly, was a ludicrous view that would make the court’s policy on coverage control weak in future processes.
But some lawyers said the courts of appeal were often drawn to arguments about the adaptation that was required in the courts due to social and technological changes.
Hayes' lawyers are pressing for that claim.
